TY  - JOUR
AU  - Braggion, Fabio
AU  - Driessen, Joost
AU  - Moore, Lyndon
T1  - The Cross-Section of Stock Returns Around the World in the Early Twentieth Century
PY  - 2025
Y1  - 2025/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rapstu/raae014
JO  - The Review of Asset Pricing Studies
JA  - Rev Asset Pric Stud
VL  - 15
IS  - 1
SP  - 46
EP  - 73
SN  - 2045-9920
AB  - We study nine equity markets between 1900 and 1925 to provide an out-of-sample test of some major asset pricing anomalies during a period in which anomalies had not been documented. We find strong evidence of momentum in almost every market. We find no evidence of long-term reversals, which, coupled with the limited presence of institutional investors, suggests that underreaction should be considered as a key aspect of behavioral theories of momentum. We also find evidence for the size effect, betting-against-beta, and the outperformance of low volatility stocks, whereas we find mixed evidence of short-term reversal. (JEL G12, G15, N20)
Y2  - 6/6/2025
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rapstu/raae014
ER  - 



